h5. Symptoms 

Currently, it's not possible to delete or remove any field configuration in JIRA, as there isn't any delete button for it, even if the 'field config' is not used anywhere. 

h5. Steps to reproduce
# Run a vanilla JIRA 6.2.3 and install Service Desk 1.2.5 
# Create a new Service Desk Project
!sd1.png|thumbnail!
# Navigate to project Administration and disable Service Desk
# Remove *Field Configuration Scheme* for the newly created project. (There will be duplicated Field Configuration Scheme due to [JSD-467|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSD-467])
# Navigate to Field Configuration. The option to delete field configuration is not available. 



{panel:title=Workaround|bgColor=#E7F4FA}
You can delete a field configuration by calling the URL:

{code:title=JIRA OnDemand}
https://<instance-name>.atlassian.net/secure/admin/DeleteFieldLayout!default.jspa?id=111
{code}
{code:title=JIRA Installed}
http://<base-url>/secure/admin/DeleteFieldLayout!default.jspa?id=10201
{code}

(i) Where (id) is the ID of the field configuration, which you can obtain it by hovering your mouse over the field config and you will see the ID at the bottom of your browser.
{panel}

