Configure an Incoming Mail server, and leave its port field blank.  Test that connection - and it passes. 

Now create a Mail Handler that uses that Incoming Mail server.  Test it.  You'll get an exception: 
{code}
Error connecting to host 'mailhost2' as user 'testuser' via protocol 'imap': javax.mail.MessagingException: 220 mailhost2.company.com ESMTP Service (Lotus Domino Release x.x.x) ready at Fri, 24 Jan 2014 11:30:09 -0600; nested exception is: com.sun.mail.iap.ConnectionException: 220 mailhost2.company.com ESMTP Service (Lotus Domino Release x.x.x) ready at Fri, 24 Jan 2014 11:30:09 -0600: 220 mailhost2.company.com ESMTP Service (Lotus Domino Release x.x.x) ready at Fri, 24 Jan 2014 11:30:09 -0600{code}

returning to the Mail server config screen - you'll notice the port # is now 25 (JRA-36714).  Supply the correct port number for the protocol you've chosen, and re-save the server and test it to ensure it can connect.  Now go back to the Mail Handler config and re-test and it works.

